Durban - KwaDabeka police are investigating a case of murder after the partially decomposed body of a woman was found in Claremont. It is believed the gruesome discovery was made by a local on Saturday to reported the matter to the police. 
Officers from the Metro and SAPS Search and Rescue found the body in a shallow grave. It was covered the a sheet. 





In a separate incident, the body of a man was found in a pit toilet in KwaNdengezi. According to police, the area was cordoned off and members of the Metro and SAPS Search and Rescue units were able to retrieve the body. An inquest was opened. 

 




In both cases, the remains were handed over to police for further investigation. 
The Mercury